 735:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** /*********************************************************************
 736:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 737:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *       SEGGER_RTT_ReadUpBuffer
 738:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 739:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Function description
 740:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Reads characters from SEGGER real-time-terminal control block
 741:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    which have been previously stored by the application.
 742:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Used to do the same operation that J-Link does, to transfer 
 743:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    RTT data via other channels, such as TCP/IP or UART.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ADMINI~1\AppData\Local\Temp\ccWpEAzr.s 			page 35


 744:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 745:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Parameters
 746:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of Up-buffer to be used.
 747:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    pBuffer      Pointer to buffer provided by target application, to copy characters from RTT-up-
 748:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferSize   Size of the target application buffer.
 749:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 750:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Return value
 751:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Number of bytes that have been read.
 752:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 753:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Additional information
 754:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    This function must not be called when J-Link might also do RTT.
 755:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    This function locks against all other RTT operations. I.e. during
 756:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    the read operation, writing is also locked.
 757:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    If only one consumer reads from the up buffer, 
 758:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    call sEGGER_RTT_ReadUpBufferNoLock() instead.
 759:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
