 808:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** /*********************************************************************
 809:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 810:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *       SEGGER_RTT_WriteWithOverwriteNoLock
 811:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 812:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Function description
 813:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Stores a specified number of characters in SEGGER RTT
 814:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    control block.
 815:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    SEGGER_RTT_WriteWithOverwriteNoLock does not lock the application 
 816:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    and overwrites data if the data does not fit into the buffer.
 817:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 818:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Parameters
 819:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of "Up"-buffer to be used (e.g. 0 for "Terminal").
 820:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    pBuffer      Pointer to character array. Does not need to point to a \0 terminated string.
 821:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    NumBytes     Number of bytes to be stored in the SEGGER RTT control block.
 822:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 823:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Notes
 824:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (1) If there is not enough space in the "Up"-buffer, data is overwritten.
 825:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (2) For performance reasons this function does not call Init()
 826:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        and may only be called after RTT has been initialized.
 827:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        Either by calling SEGGER_RTT_Init() or calling another RTT API function first.
 828:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (3) Do not use SEGGER_RTT_WriteWithOverwriteNoLock if a J-Link 
 829:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        connection reads RTT data.
 830:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
 831:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** void SEGGER_RTT_WriteWithOverwriteNoLock(unsigned BufferIndex, const void* pBuffer, unsigned NumByt
