1151:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1152:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Function description
1153:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Stores a specified number of characters in SEGGER RTT control block in a <Down> buffer.
1154:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1155:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Parameters
1156:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of "Up"-buffer to be used (e.g. 0 for "Terminal").
1157:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    pBuffer      Pointer to character array. Does not need to point to a \0 terminated string.
1158:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    NumBytes     Number of bytes to be stored in the SEGGER RTT control block.
1159:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1160:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Return value
1161:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Number of bytes which have been stored in the "Down"-buffer.
1162:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1163:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Notes
1164:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (1) Data is stored according to buffer flags.
1165:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1166:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Additional information
1167:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    This function must not be called when J-Link might also do RTT.
1168:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    This function locks against all other RTT operations. I.e. during
1169:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    the write operation, writing from the application is also locked.
1170:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    If only one consumer writes to the down buffer, 
1171:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    call SEGGER_RTT_WriteDownBufferNoLock() instead.
1172:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
