1242:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1243:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Function description
1244:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Stores a single character/byte in SEGGER RTT buffer.
1245:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    SEGGER_RTT_PutCharSkipNoLock does not lock the application and
1246:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    skips the byte, if it does not fit into the buffer.
1247:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1248:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Parameters
1249:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of "Up"-buffer to be used (e.g. 0 for "Terminal").
1250:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    c            Byte to be stored.
1251:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1252:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Return value
1253:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Number of bytes which have been stored in the "Up"-buffer.
1254:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1255:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Notes
1256:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (1) If there is not enough space in the "Up"-buffer, the character is dropped.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ADMINI~1\AppData\Local\Temp\ccWpEAzr.s 			page 60


1257:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (2) For performance reasons this function does not call Init()
1258:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        and may only be called after RTT has been initialized.
1259:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        Either by calling SEGGER_RTT_Init() or calling another RTT API function first.
1260:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
